ppunctuations.ppunctuation:
Executed: not quite regularly.
Usage: not always logical.
Dividers:
I. Colon;
Colon with short red lines above, below and in the middle (used throughout the text)
II. Four dot asterisk (e.g. fols.: 9rb, l.5; 15vb, l.13; 16va, l.2; 17va, l.14; fol. 35rb, l.5);  
nine dot asterisk (used throughout the text);
four nine dot asterisks (esp. fol. 35ra, l.10).
III. Chain of black and red left-pointing chevrons (esp. fol.  35ra, ls. 11-12);
long black line (esp. fol. 35rb, l.6).

rubrications.rubrication:
Nomina sacra;
incipit - the trinitarian formula  at the beginning of the text (fol. 2ra) and elsewhere (e.g. fols.: 4ra, ls. 6-7; 5rb, ls. 5-6; 15va, ls. 8-10; 16rb, ls. 15-17; 23vb, ls. 8-10); 
two groups of lines in the incipit page (fol. 2r): the first on the column “a”, ls. 7-8, the second on the column “b”, ls. 7-9; 
some lines at paragraph beginning in fols. 23ra, ls.16-17, 32ra, ls. 2-3;
the horizontal dashes above and below Ethiopic numerals; 
elements of the punctuation signs;
the words “sänbät” and “ʾǝḫud”;
names of the donors, and some other passages (s., e.g., fol. 23r).
